							</tr> 
							<tr>
							  <td width='210px' bgcolor='#077A77' class="mtitle" ><font  color='#ffffff'><b>Advantages</b></font></td>
							  <td width='210px' bgcolor='#077A77' class="mtitle"><font  color='#ffffff'><b>Disadvantages</b></font></td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
							  <td bgcolor='#EFF8F7' valign="top">Suitable in all topologies where multiple routers are required.</td>
							  <td bgcolor='#EFF8F7' valign="top">Can be more complex to implement.</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
							  <td bgcolor='#ffffff' valign="top">Generally independent of the network size.</td>
							  <td bgcolor='#ffffff' valign="top">Less secure. Additional configuration settings are required to secure.</td>
							</tr> 
							<tr>
							  <td bgcolor='#EFF8F7' valign="top">Automatically adapts topology to reroute traffic if possible.</td>
							  <td bgcolor='#EFF8F7' valign="top">Route depends on the current topology.</td>
							</tr>	
							<tr>
							  <td bgcolor='#ffffff' valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
							  <td bgcolor='#ffffff' valign="top">Requires additional CPU, RAM, and link bandwidth.</td>
							</tr>
